    q: 'What SIC codes should an SPV use?',
    a: 'Lenders want the company recorded against property-only standard industrial classification (SIC) codes, most commonly 68100, 68209, 68320 or 68201, which describe buying, letting and managing property. Keep the codes to property alone. A company that also lists a trading activity reads as a mixed business and narrows the lenders willing to fund it.',
